article:
This page lists the holders of the office of '[[Prime Minister of Egypt|Prime
Minister]] of [[Egypt]]'. The office was created when Egypt's Council of
Ministers was established in August 1878, after Khedive Isma'il Pasha agreed to
turn his powers over to a cabinet modeled after those of Europe. Nubar Pasha was
thus Egypt's first Prime Minister in the modern sense. Prior to that, Egypt had
traditional Muslim-style viziers. The current Interim Prime Minister of Egypt is
Hazem Al Beblawi, since 16 July 2013.
